==English==
===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]] /'blægard/

===Noun===
'''blackguard, blaggard'''
# A scoundrel; an unprincipled contemptible person; an untrustworthy person. Usually, only used to refer to a male person.

A blackguard may also refer to a man who uses foul language in front of a women, typically a women of high standing in society.